HEADWORD: Eyewitness
<hw>Eye"wit`ness</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who sees a
thing done; one who has ocular view of anything.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>We . . . were <qex>eyewitnesses</qex> of his majesty.</q>
<rj><qau>2 Pet. i. 16.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

